														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4109414">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Adult tube worms anchor themselves near sulfurous vents, opening their bodies to infection by <strong>chemotropic</strong> single-celled archaea.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Do you mean &quot;chemotrophic&quot; here?</p>
<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemotropism">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemotropism</a></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Chemotropism is growth of organisms such as bacteria and plants, navigated by chemical stimulus from outside of the organism or organism's part.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemotroph">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemotroph</a></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Chemotrophs are organisms that obtain energy by the oxidation of electron donors in their environments.</p>
</blockquote>

							</div>

								
					
